Global Short Fiber Reinforced Thermoplastic Composite Market Insights
Short Fiber Reinforced Thermoplastic Composite Market size was valued at USD 3.5 Billion in 2022 and is projected to reach USD 6.5 Billion by 2030, growing at a CAGR of 8.5% from 2024 to 2030.

Short Fiber Reinforced Thermoplastic Composite Market Overview
The Short Fiber Reinforced Thermoplastic Composite (SFRT) market has gained significant momentum with an increasing demand for lightweight materials in various industries such as automotive, aerospace, and electronics. As of 2024, the global market size for SFRT composites is valued at approximately USD 2.6 billion and is expected to grow at a CAGR of 8.4% from 2025 to 2030. This growth is primarily driven by the need for enhanced material properties like high strength-to-weight ratio, cost efficiency, and processability. Furthermore, ongoing advancements in processing technologies and the expanding adoption of thermoplastic composites in manufacturing are contributing to the growth trajectory. The rise of electric vehicles and lightweight aircraft is also driving the demand for SFRT in various applications.

